  "texts": [
    "Poll results could therefore be thought-provoking and incite voters to critically engage with the most popular view.",
    "This cognitive mechanism is more sophisticated than the well-known 'bandwagon effect' according to which people are likely to side with the most popular opinion to be on the winning side.",
    "It is not about mere mimetism, but rather about the persuasive power of self-generated reasons.",
    "The process of thinking of reasons behind a position makes the position more compelling; what triggers this thought process and internal deliberation is the knowledge of what others think.",
    "This effect does not, however, always lead to a convergence effect."
  ],
